textDisplay:
https://youtu.be/JEjaip1ePYM

Dear American friends, I know what you are going through.

We have lived it and we are still living it

on our skin.

It is painful, it tears your soul to see a whole go away

elderly generation.

With them we are not only losing our grandparents, uncles, fathers, we are also losing our past, our family memories.

So I understand your anguish.

But with a little patience you will come out too.

You have to stay at home and reduce your expenses to just buying

of basic necessities.

Use masks and gloves and keep your distance between them.

And lastly, whoever believes it, declaim a prayer every now and then.

I leave you a post, an eighteen year old boy from Rome.

His name is Jacopo and he lives in the splendid Piazza Navona.

To be close to his city, to his people, he climbed onto the terrace of his palace and, looking at a deserted Piazza Navona,

he took his own electric guitar and performed Deborah's Theme, written by Ennio Morricone, as the main motif of Sergio Leone's film "One Upon A Time In America".

I'm sure it will bring luck to you too.

We Italians, betrayed by this Europe of merchants, are close to you.

Because, as Italians, we are part of you.

God bless you.
